-- China Plans to Build National Freeway, High-Speed Rail Network, Daily Says
-- B y   T a t i a n a   L a u
-- 2010-11-09T00:04:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/china-plans-to-build-national-freeway-high-speed-rail-network-daily-says.html
China will build an 85,000-kilometer
national freeway network and a 40,000-kilometer high-speed
railway network as part of its next five-year plan, China Daily
reported, citing Wu Xiao, an official from the National
Development and Reform Commission.  The railway network will link 500,000 people and the
freeway network will connect all cities with a population of
more than 200,000, the newspaper said, citing Wu.  To contact the reporter on this story:
